==English==
[[Image:Eo-scale of justice.gif|thumb|right|A balance (scale).]]
[[Image:One-balanced-rock.jpg|thumb|right|A rock balanced on one corner.]]

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|frm|en}} {{term|balance|lang=frm}}, from {{etyl|LL.}} *{{term||bilancia}}, from (accusative form of) {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|bilanx||two-scaled|lang=la}}, from {{term|bi-|lang=la}} + {{term|lanx||lang=la|plate, scale}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈbaləns/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈbæləns/}}
* {{audio|en-us-balance.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# A pair of [[scales]].
# {{obsolete|astrology}} [[Libra]].
# {{context|watchmaking}} A device used to regulate the speed of a watch, clock etc.
# A weight placed on a scale to provide equilibrium; something of equal importance or value.
#: ''Blair thought he could provide a useful '''balance''' to Bush's policies.''
# {{uncountable}} [[equilibrium|Equilibrium]]; a state in which opposing forces cancel each other out.
# {{uncountable}} Mental equilibrium; [[calmness]], a state of remaining clear-headed and unperturbed.
# {{uncountable}}  [[support|Support]] for both viewpoints, substances etc or neither; [[neutrality]].
# Apparent harmony in arts, design etc. between differing colours, sounds, etc.
# The overall result of conflicting forces, opinions etc.; the influence which ultimately "weighs" more than others.
#: ''The '''balance''' of power finally lay with the Royalist forces.''
#: ''I think the '''balance''' of opinion is that we should get out while we're ahead.''
# {{accounting}} A [[list]] accounting for the [[debits]] on one side, and for the [[credits]] on the other.
# The result of such a procedure; the difference between credit and debit of an account.
#: ''I just need to nip to a bank and check my '''balance'''.''

====Synonyms====
* (''scales''): pair of scales, [[scales]], [[weighing machine]], [[weighbridge]] (''for vehicles'')
* (''equilibrium''): [[equilibrium]]
* (''support for both viewpoints''): [[disinterest]], [[even-handedness]], [[fairness]], [[impartiality]], [[neutrality]], [[non-partisanship]]
* (''list of credits and debits''): [[account]]

====Antonyms====
